# Use Case 001 - Add Cities

## Summary
User adds cities which are used when creating Schools

## Actor
Registered user

## Precondition
1. Registered user is authenticated.
2. Registered user is member of Admin role.
3. States are seeded by system. 

## Main Sequence
1. User clicks Admin drop down menu in nav bar.
2. User selects Add Cities nav bar item.
3. System shows Add Cities form.
4. User enters one or more (max 100) cities:
    - Name  (required)
    - State (required, drop down)
    > Note: city data is validated as user enters data:<br/>
        - City max 100 characters <br/>
        - State is two letter abbreviation.<br/>
5. If no validation errors, Save button is enabled.
6. User clicks Save.
7. Server validates form data.
8. If server validation succeeds, Cities are persisted.
9. Notification toast saying Save is successful.

## Alternative Sequences
4A1. Validarion fails. The system shows the error message to the user.
5A1. User clicks Cancel. System navigates back to Home page. No data is modified.
8A1. Server validation fails. The system shows the error message to the user. Notification toast saying Save failed.

## Persistence Notes
When a City is added:
- Database sets created date to the current UTC time.
- Database auto assigns surrogate key.
    
## Business Rules
Cities are duplicates if:
    - Names and States are equal.
    - Duplicates not allowed.